By Default Redis Does not support Windows OS but you can run it using github

=> Go to below URL
https://github.com/MicrosoftArchive/redis

=> Now Search for Below Line ( It will be 3rd Line of below heading )
Redis on Windows
You can download the latest unsigned binaries and the unsigned MSI installer from the release page.

=> Click on release page
=> Now Below URL will Open
https://github.com/microsoftarchive/redis/releases

=> Now Download Zip file
=> Now Extract this zip file

=> Open your Envirnoment Varible click on System variable Edit Path and add the path of your redis server
=>Now Open your Cmd and run server using below command
redis-server

=> Open another cmd and run client using below command
redis-cli

Now your redis client will start type Ping on client it will return Pong as a response
